 * {@code goog.Promise.resolve(value).then(onFulfilled, onRejected)}, but it
 * avoids creating an unnecessary wrapper Promise when {@code value} is already
 * thenable.
 *
 * @param {?(goog.Thenable<TYPE>|Thenable|TYPE)} value
